Terrorist Threat Condition HIGH RISK: Credible intelligence indicates that there is a high risk of a local terrorist attack but a specific target has not been identified.
Threat Condition Critical Facilities Protective Action Continue all precautions from lower Threat Level.
Â¨ Announce Threat Level HIGH to all employees and explain expected actions.
Â¨ Place emergency response teams on notice.
Â¨ Activate the operations center if required.
Â¨ Monitor world and local events.
Pass on credible threat intelligence to key personnel.
Â¨ Ensure appropriate security measures are in place and functioning properly.
Â¨ Instruct employees to report suspicious activities, packages and people.
Â¨ Search all personal bags, parcels to the extent of the law and require personnel to pass through magnetometer, if available.
Â¨ Restrict vehicle parking close to buildings.
Â¨ Inspect intrusion detection systems, lighting, security fencing and locking systems.
Â¨ Inspect all deliveries and consider accepting shipments only at off-site locations.
Â¨ Remind employees to expect delays and baggage searches.
Local Government Actions Continue all precautions from lower Threat Level.
Â¨ Announce Threat Condition HIGH to employees and public and explain expected actions to be taken.
Â¨ Test Communication plan.
Â¨ Restrict or control access to governmental buildings, critical facilities and infrastructure.
Â¨ Erect outside barricades, security checks to deny access to underground parking areas, loading docks and building entrances.
Â¨ Require identification, sign-in and escorts as required.
Â¨ Restrict parking areas located close to buildings or critical facilities.
Â¨ Remove trash containers, dumpsters and mailboxes located near government buildings and facilities.
Â¨ Closely monitor available security and intelligence data from state and local law enforcement agencies.
Â¨ Instruct employees to be especially watchful for suspicious or unattended packages and articles received through the mail service.
Â¨ Inspect buildings and parking areas for suspicious packages.
Â¨ Implement rumor control to avoid public panic.
Â¨ Employ appropriate security at airports, dams, public utilities and critical facilities.
Â¨ Based on threat assessment, define level, scope and role of emergency response personnel.
Â¨ Secure and regularly inspect all buildings, vehicles, and parking and storage areas for intrusion.
Â¨ Conduct 100% verification of deliveries and restrict shipments.
Public Response Guidelines Continue all precautions from lower Threat Level.
Â¨ Resume normal activities but expect some delays, baggage searches and restrictions as a result of heightened security at public buildings and facilities.
Â¨ Continue to monitor world and local events as well as local government threat advisories.
Â¨ Report suspicious activities at or near critical facilities to state and local law enforcement agencies by calling 911.
Â¨ Avoid leaving unattended packages or briefcases in public areas.
Â¨ Inventory and organize emergency supply kits and discuss emergency plans with family members.
Reevaluate meeting location based on threat.
Â¨ Consider taking reasonable personal security precautions.
Be alert to your surroundings, avoid placing yourself in a vulnerable situation and monitor the activities of your family members.
Â¨ Maintain close contact with your family and neighbors to ensure their safety and emotional welfare.
