Terrorist Threat Condition Elevated risk of terrorist attack but a specific region of the USA or target has not been identified.
Threat Condition
Critical Facilities Protective Action Continue all precautions from lower Threat Level.
Â¨ Announce Threat Condition ELEVATED to employees.
Review vulnerability and threat assessments and revise as needed.
Â¨ Identify and monitor governmental information sharing sources for warnings and alerts.
Â¨ Update and test call list for emergency response teams and key employees.
Â¨ Review and coordinate and update mutual aid agreements with other critical facilities and government agencies.
Â¨ Establish and monitor active and passive security measures.
Â¨ Review employee training on security precautions (bomb threat procedures, reporting suspicious packages, activities and people).
Â¨ Conduct communications checks to ensure radio contact can be established.
Local Government Actions Continue all precautions from lower Threat Level.
Â¨ Announce Threat Condition ELEVATED to employees and to the public.
Â¨ Review physical security plans for critical facilities.
Â¨ Assess potential terrorist targets and develop plans to counter-act an attack.
Â¨ Conduct vulnerability assessments of each critical facility and governmental building.
Estimate the consequence of loss and assign a priority for their protection.
Â¨ Ensure all buildings are secured to prevent theft or tampering.
Â¨ Conduct physical inspections of buildings for suspicious unattended packages.
Â¨ Develop a cadre of trained volunteers.
Â¨ Closely monitor current news events and state and federal terrorist advisories.
Â¨ Keep the public informed on current threat conditions and advisories.
Â¨ Coordinate with adjacent municipalities for mutual aid support in the event of a disaster or terrorist threat.
Â¨ Conduct tabletop and functional exercises to ensure that response plans are understood and current.
Â¨ Review existing physical security measures employed, and install intrusion detection and passive systems as funding permits.
Â¨ Conduct weekly radio communication checks.
Public Response Guidelines Continue all precautions from lower Threat Level.
Â¨ Continue normal activities, but report suspicious activities to local law enforcement agencies.
Â¨ Take a first aid class.
Â¨ Become active in your local Neighborhood Crime Watch program.
Â¨ Network with your family, neighbors and community for mutual support during a disaster or terrorist attack.
Â¨ Learn what critical facilities are located in your community and report suspicious activities at or near these sites.
Â¨ Attend your local emergency planning committee meeting to learn more about local hazards.
(Call the city/town emergency manager to learn dates and locations of the meetings.)
Â¨ Increase individual or family emergency preparedness through training, maintaining good physical fitness and health, and storing food, water and emergency supplies.
