Terrorist Threat Condition GUARDED: General Risk with no credible threats to specific targets.
Threat Condition Critical Facilities Protective Action Continue all precautions from lower Threat Level.
Â¨ Ensure that key leaders are familiar with the emergency response and business resumption plans.
Â¨ Review, update and routinely exercise for functional areas of the plan.
Â¨ Review and update the call list for emergency response teams.
Â¨ Develop or review Mutual Aid agreements with other facilities and/or with local government for use during emergencies.
Â¨ Review physical security precautions to prevent theft, unauthorized entry or destruction of property.
Have you provided for: a) Employee picture ID badges? b) Background checks on all employees? c) Access control and locking of high security areas at all times? d) All security keys marked `Do Not Duplicate'? e) Surveillance cameras? f) Back-up power? g) An alarm system?
Local Government Actions Continue all precautions from lower Threat Level.
Â¨ Estimate the threat vulnerability of each critical facility ant the countermeasures required to protect them.
Â¨ Ensure that each department is familiar with their assigned responsibilities during a disaster, as shown in the plan, and are prepared to respond.
Â¨ Review communications plans to ensure the call-down procedures are current and accurate.
Â¨ Conduct emergency management training and exercise emergency response plans.
Â¨ Ensure all emergency management and response functions are adequately staffed.
Recruit and train volunteers to augment full time staff.
Â¨ Actively support the Neighborhood Watch, Community Emergency Response Team and Amateur Radio Emergency Service programs.
Â¨ Remind citizens and employees to be alert for suspicious packages, activities, vehicles and people and report these occurrences to the proper authorities.
Â¨ Secure buildings, unused rooms, storage areas, equipment and vehicles to prevent theft, tampering or destruction.
Â¨ Evaluate information available on public websites that could compromise security.
Â¨ Encourage all citizens and employees to have necessary immunizations.
Public Response Guidelines Continue all precautions from lower Threat Level.
Â¨ Continue normal activities but be watchful for suspicious activities.
Report criminal activity to local law enforcement.
Â¨ Monitor local and national news for terrorist alerts.
Â¨ Review family emergency plans.
Â¨ Increase family emergency preparedness by purchasing supplies, food and storing water.
Â¨ Be familiar with local natural and technological (man made) hazards in your community.
Â¨ Increase individual or family emergency preparedness through training, maintaining good physical fitness and health, and storing food, water and emergency supplies.
Â¨ Update immunizations.
Â¨ Volunteer to assist and support the community emergency response agencies.
